        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">Dire Charm looks really, really nice.</P><P>However...</P><P>To get Dire Charm, you must be 59th and you must have spent 27 skill points to get it. </P><P>One Skill point = the exp needed to go from 51 to 52 once.  </P><P>In other words, you must be 59th and have repeated 51-52 21(twenty-seven) times.  </P><P>Doesn't this seem like the ultimate carrot at the end of the never-ending stick?</P><P><BR>Nanaelil D'Vorn<BR>55th Necromancer<BR>Scorned, Ignored, Left Behind</P><P>If Darinar is correct, then not only will I have to level from 1st to 60th, but I will also have to re-earn and trade in the exp required to level from 1st to 60th.</P><P>In otherwords: to get Dire Charm, one must level from 1st to 60th twice.</P><P>/sigh  </P><P>PS...all mathmatical corrections brought to my (fleeting) attention by <BR>Darinar.</P><P>Edited by - nanaelil on 12/04/2001  07:29:40</P><P>Edited by - nanaelil on 12/04/2001  07:32:32</font></td>
