        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">Some could argue that for a permanent charm it would be worth it, considering they are gaining exp at L60 on raids and helping friends exp farm anyway.</P><P>I would guess that the typical raiding L60 player (not a casual player who does a raid or two, but one who is in a raiding guild and raids ~3 times a week) will get slightly less than half of those skill points without changing their routine or even trying.</P><P>Also, getting the exp from L50-60 over again for a L60 player would be somewhat easier than doing it the first time through since they will be in groups killing higher exp mobs than the average sub-59 player.</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
