        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">Agreed, that isn't a very good measure of the time it will take.  I had troubles getting out of level 7 way the hell back when but now I root dot mobs that would take you from level 1 to level 8 at least in just one kill.</P><P>However he is definately right to be worried about the amount of time it will take to acquire the skills.  So lets put it in a different perspective.</P><P>I'm sure those of us who are 59/60 are rather familiar with the superhell level that is 59.  Well to get the exp for the 6 points in general abilities is equivalent to level 59 all over again and filling up the bar of 60 on top of that.  Then to get the exp for the 12 points in archtype abilities is equivalent another 3 full trips through level 59 again.  Now you just need to earn enough exp to get through 59 two *more* times in order to get one of the 9 point class abilities.</P><P>That is one shitload of exp before you see your first class ability.</P><P>***However***</P><P>All this is assuming that a single skills point is roughly equivalent to exp needed to go through level 51.  Many other things that were stated at that time have changed so this might have as well.</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
