        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">Dire Charm: (1 skill level - cost 9 skill points) - This ability allows the Necromancer to charm an NPC without fear that the NPC will break the charm (charm will end only when the Necromancer leaves the zone or logs out) without the memorization of a spell or the expenditure of mana. <b><u>All of the usual restriction for charm spells apply to this ability as well, except in regards to duration</b></u>. The Refresh Timer for this ability is 72 minutes (one day of game time).</P><P>-=-=-=-=-</P><P>You wont be able to charm anything any more powerful then you currently already can. The only differance is that the charm will last until you leave, and doesn't cost mana or a spell slot.</P><P>My opinion: Good? Yes. Worth all of the exp work? No. It gets a "loopty doo" considering its incredible cost.</P><P>So, now we can run around Rathe Mountains with a giant skeleton without the mob breaking charm & emberassing us in front of the newbs. Uber.</P><P>~Mysk</P><P>P.S. 72 minute refresh time. LOL...</P><P>Pet dies in dungeon group.<BR>Groupie tells the group, "Quick, DC the add!"<BR>--Your target resisted your Charm spell!--<BR>Necromancer tells the group, "#@$!"</P><P>--<BR>[52 Heretic] Mysk (Dark Elf) SERVER: Tunare</P><P>"When preparing your zombies, fill their body with gunpowder.  That way when the heroes set them on fire they will get a nasty surprize."</P><P>Edited by - Mysk on 12/04/2001  11:16:20<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
