        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">Allaxul Darksoul, </P><P>While grinding out the necessary exp to get the 27 skill points required to obtain Dire Charm, players have raised a good point:  If you are in a good 55+ group, then the exp/per mob will be much, much higher than the exp you got while grinding your way through level 20+ groups.  </P><P>Ergo, while the exp required to get Dire Charm is significant, it will go much, much faster than the original grind through 60th.  </P><P>time will tell... </P><P><BR>Nanaelil D'Vorn<BR>55th Necromancer<BR>Scorned, Ignored, Left Behind<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
